CYP Inhibition Assay: Incubation of phenacetin, diclofenac, dextromethorphan, mephenotoin, albendazole and testosterone with human liver microsomes in the presence of in each case eight different concentrations of a compound formula (B) (as potential inhibitor) is carried out on a incubator shaker at 37 C. Standard incubation mixtures comprise NADPH and substrates in 100 mM phosphate buffer (pH 7.4) in a total volume of 200 l. Test compound are dissolved in acetonitrile. Incubated with pooled human liver microsomes at 37 C. for a defined time. The reactions are stopped by adding 100 l of acetonitrile in which a suitable internal standard is always present. Precipitated proteins are removed by centrifugation, and the supernatants analyzed by LC-MS/MS.
